Text.SourceString: Whoa, look who’s finally here!//The new farmer, right? I’m <NPCName>Frank</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Whoa, look who’s finally here!//The new farmer, right? I’m <NPCName>Frank</>.

Text.LocalizedString: Folks at the Tavern have been talking about you.//You should stop by sometime.

Text.SourceString: The Tavern is pretty old. I hope the town doesn’t ever tear it down to build some shiny new one.//That’s why we do our best to take good care of it, repainting the building and all.
Text.LocalizedString: The Tavern is pretty old. I hope the town doesn’t ever tear it down to build some shiny new one.//That’s why we do our best to take good care of it, repainting the building and all.

Text.SourceString: It’s where I grew up, you know.

Text.SourceString: Oh, gee! Have you been by my house lately?//The lot gets unkempt so fast.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, gee! Have you been by my house lately?//The lot gets unkempt so fast.

Text.SourceString: It’s really a waste of time to clean it up.//Maybe if I plant a garden, other people will help keep it up. I’m too busy to do it all alone.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s really a waste of time to clean it up.//Maybe if I plant a garden, other people will help keep it up. I’m too busy to do it all alone.

Text.SourceString: I can’t imagine living anywhere but here.//But I do miss the city every now and then.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t imagine living anywhere but here.//But I do miss the city every now and then.

Text.SourceString: Only to visit, that is.//<portrait=happy>You know, two or three days. A week, tops.
Text.LocalizedString: Only to visit, that is.//<portrait=happy>You know, two or three days. A week, tops.

Text.SourceString: I’m always trying out new recipes for the Tavern, so make sure to visit often.//You really don’t want to miss anything!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m always trying out new recipes for the Tavern, so make sure to visit often.//You really don’t want to miss anything!

Text.SourceString: We’re closed tomorrow. Oh, but if you need me, just pop by my house.//I’ll be there all day.
Text.LocalizedString: We’re closed tomorrow. Oh, but if you need me, just pop by my house.//I’ll be there all day.

Text.SourceString: I cook at home.//<portrait=happy>I love it, and frankly, I’m good at it! Ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I cook at home.//<portrait=happy>I love it, and frankly, I’m good at it! Ha!

Text.SourceString: If somebody asked, sure, I’d sing.//I mean, why the heck not!
Text.LocalizedString: If somebody asked, sure, I’d sing.//I mean, why the heck not!

Text.SourceString: Hmm… Maybe I can get <NPCName>Theo</> to sing with me.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… Maybe I can get <NPCName>Theo</> to sing with me.

Text.SourceString: When I first took over the Tavern, the town gave me a recipe book.//You couldn’t ask for a more thoughtful community!
Text.LocalizedString: When I first took over the Tavern, the town gave me a recipe book.//You couldn’t ask for a more thoughtful community!

Text.SourceString: I mix my own drinks at the bar sometimes.//No complaints so far.
Text.LocalizedString: I mix my own drinks at the bar sometimes.//No complaints so far.

Text.SourceString: Heh heh heh… Classic! That’s a knee-slapper!//<portrait=normal>You know the funniest jokes.
Text.LocalizedString: Heh heh heh… Classic! That’s a knee-slapper!//<portrait=normal>You know the funniest jokes.

Text.SourceString: The cost of living is really low on Coral Island.//I don’t think you need to make a lot to live comfortably.
Text.LocalizedString: The cost of living is really low on Coral Island.//I don’t think you need to make a lot to live comfortably.

Text.SourceString: The islanders here want to see you succeed.//That’s what makes this place special.
Text.LocalizedString: The islanders here want to see you succeed.//That’s what makes this place special.

Text.SourceString: If you surround yourself with positive people, soon enough, positivity will be second nature.//I believe that.
Text.LocalizedString: If you surround yourself with positive people, soon enough, positivity will be second nature.//I believe that.

Text.SourceString: Do you need help?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you need help?

Text.SourceString: Hello, hello, hello!
Text.LocalizedString: Hello, hello, hello!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Leah’s</> trying to make it big on the internet.//Don’t ask me. I don’t know what it means either.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes, she asks if she can record me cooking. For “content,” she says.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Leah’s</> trying to make it big on the internet.//Don’t ask me. I don’t know what it means either.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes, she asks if she can record me cooking. For “content,” she says.

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind.//<portrait=surprised>Who knows? I might become famous! Ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind.//<portrait=surprised>Who knows? I might become famous! Ha ha.

Text.SourceString: Make sure to rest and drink plenty of water, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure to rest and drink plenty of water, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: With the work you do, every day must be exhausting.
Text.LocalizedString: With the work you do, every day must be exhausting.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Noah</> and I used to run around the island, terrorizing our parents.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Noah</> and I used to run around the island, terrorizing our parents.

Text.SourceString: Now I have two cats, and they’re doing it to me.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha. Oh, how the tables have turned!
Text.LocalizedString: Now I have two cats, and they’re doing it to me.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha. Oh, how the tables have turned!

Text.SourceString: Out of all us siblings, I was the one with the tendency to go rogue.//<portrait=surprised>Can you tell? Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: Out of all us siblings, I was the one with the tendency to go rogue.//<portrait=surprised>Can you tell? Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: I guess I grew out of it…
Text.LocalizedString: I guess I grew out of it…

Text.SourceString: I left the island to go to college some years ago.//It was a fun time.
Text.LocalizedString: I left the island to go to college some years ago.//It was a fun time.

Text.SourceString: But as soon as I graduated, I knew I needed to come back.//I felt like I didn’t belong in the big city, you know?//Was never home to me.
Text.LocalizedString: But as soon as I graduated, I knew I needed to come back.//I felt like I didn’t belong in the big city, you know?//Was never home to me.

Text.SourceString: I learned to cook from Mom. But I didn’t actually <Italic>cook</> cook until I went away to college.//I didn’t have much choice. I missed Mom’s food, and I was just too far from home.
Text.LocalizedString: I learned to cook from Mom. But I didn’t actually <Italic>cook</> cook until I went away to college.//I didn’t have much choice. I missed Mom’s food, and I was just too far from home.

Text.LocalizedString: What was I supposed to do? Go home? Ha ha!

Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Noah’s</> had glasses since grade school.//You know, you seem to be asking a lot of questions about <NPCName>Noah</>.//Interesting!

Text.LocalizedString: Can you say “frankly” when your name is <NPCName>Frank</>?

Text.SourceString: Chill, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s Thursday!
Text.LocalizedString: Chill, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s Thursday!

Text.SourceString: Bookkeeping isn’t one of my strengths.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s just so tedious.
Text.LocalizedString: Bookkeeping isn’t one of my strengths.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s just so tedious.

Text.SourceString: I’d much rather do physical work. Be the face of the business.//Entertain people, you know what I mean?
Text.LocalizedString: I’d much rather do physical work. Be the face of the business.//Entertain people, you know what I mean?

Text.SourceString: My brother likes doing the tedious stuff, anyway.//He sits in the office and just goes to town with the numbers. People, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: My brother likes doing the tedious stuff, anyway.//He sits in the office and just goes to town with the numbers. People, eh?

Text.SourceString: My brother takes care of most of the back-of-the-house things, running Fishensips.
Text.LocalizedString: My brother takes care of most of the back-of-the-house things, running Fishensips.

Text.SourceString: You know, like purchasing, collecting receipts…//<portrait=annoyed>Oh, and filing our taxes. Blech.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, like purchasing, collecting receipts…//<portrait=annoyed>Oh, and filing our taxes. Blech.

Text.LocalizedString: Chill, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s Sunday!

Text.LocalizedString: Pufferfish has an international reputation for finding secluded islands to set up drilling operations at.

Text.LocalizedString: I just hope they don’t drill here.

Text.LocalizedString: My mom’s full name is <NPCName>Beatrice</>. And mine is <NPCName>Franklin</>, after Dad. Is <PlayerName>$player</> your full name?

Text.SourceString: I was there on a school holiday with my ex. Don’t talk about her too much around <NPCName>Erika</>, though.//<portrait=surprised>She’s not a big fan of the story. Kidding!
Text.LocalizedString: I was there on a school holiday with my ex. Don’t talk about her too much around <NPCName>Erika</>, though.//<portrait=surprised>She’s not a big fan of the story. Kidding!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Paul’s</> been telling me that <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> are waking them up at night.//<portrait=concerned>I asked if he was positive it’s my cats and not wild animals.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Paul’s</> been telling me that <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> are waking them up at night.//<portrait=concerned>I asked if he was positive it’s my cats and not wild animals.

Text.SourceString: Hard to believe, to be honest. My cats rarely go out.//<portrait=normal>But hey, maybe it was them. I don’t know.
Text.LocalizedString: Hard to believe, to be honest. My cats rarely go out.//<portrait=normal>But hey, maybe it was them. I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: I hope you’re planting avocados this year, <PlayerName>$player</>. I don’t like the imported ones! They just don’t hit the same note.//<portrait=normal>Know what I mean?
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you’re planting avocados this year, <PlayerName>$player</>. I don’t like the imported ones! They just don’t hit the same note.//<portrait=normal>Know what I mean?

Text.SourceString: It breaks my heart to even think about it, but I constantly worry about Mom with a house this big, especially when <NPCName>Noah</> moves out.//What if she slips in the kitchen or something?
Text.LocalizedString: It breaks my heart to even think about it, but I constantly worry about Mom with a house this big, especially when <NPCName>Noah</> moves out.//What if she slips in the kitchen or something?

Text.SourceString: I suppose you’re right. She did raise four kids.//<portrait=concerned>She’s a strong woman! But still… She’s not as young as she used to be.
Text.LocalizedString: I suppose you’re right. She did raise four kids.//<portrait=concerned>She’s a strong woman! But still… She’s not as young as she used to be.

Text.SourceString: You look concerned. What’s going on?
Text.LocalizedString: You look concerned. What’s going on?

Text.SourceString: Yeah. Come out here more often, will ya? Hang out with us.//It’s no good working too hard anyway, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah. Come out here more often, will ya? Hang out with us.//It’s no good working too hard anyway, eh?

Text.SourceString: Ha! Oops!
Text.LocalizedString: Ha! Oops!

Text.SourceString: Yeah. Come out here more often, will ya? Hang out with us.//It’s no good being alone with your thoughts too long.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah. Come out here more often, will ya? Hang out with us.//It’s no good being alone with your thoughts too long.

Special.SourceString: I don’t know exactly. Just life, I guess.
Special.LocalizedString: I don’t know exactly. Just life, I guess.

135.Question: R3

Text.SourceString: I saw my cats sunbathing in front of <NPCName>Sam</>’s the other day. It was so cute.//I wished I could sunbathe with them, but I had to work.
Text.LocalizedString: I saw my cats sunbathing in front of <NPCName>Sam</>’s the other day. It was so cute.//I wished I could sunbathe with them, but I had to work.

Text.SourceString: We should crank up the music a little in here. What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: We should crank up the music a little in here. What do you think?

Text.SourceString: Fishensips… <NpcName>Noah</> and I came up with that.//This place didn’t use to have a name. People just called it the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>It wasn’t a big deal, ’cause there’s only one in Starlet Town.
Text.LocalizedString: Fishensips… <NpcName>Noah</> and I came up with that.//This place didn’t use to have a name. People just called it the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>It wasn’t a big deal, ’cause there’s only one in Starlet Town.

Text.SourceString: The fish on the rooftop –now, that was me. A fish sipping a drink! Ha! Silly, right?//<portrait=happy>That was all my idea. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: The fish on the rooftop –now, that was me. A fish sipping a drink! Ha! Silly, right?//<portrait=happy>That was all my idea. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: We get a lot of requests to sell mooncakes. Mom’s mooncakes.//<portrait=annoyed>I don’t know… Maybe I can sell them on an as-available basis. That way, Mom doesn’t need to bake them <Italic>all</> the time.//<portrait=concerned>Good idea, bad idea? What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: We get a lot of requests to sell mooncakes. Mom’s mooncakes.//<portrait=annoyed>I don’t know… Maybe I can sell them on an as-available basis. That way, Mom doesn’t need to bake them <Italic>all</> the time.//<portrait=concerned>Good idea, bad idea? What do you think?

Text.SourceString: You know the Beach Cleanup Festival? I think it would be much better if we had a barbecue at the end.//<portrait=happy>Corn, some fish…maybe watermelon?//Doesn’t it sound good?
Text.LocalizedString: You know the Beach Cleanup Festival? I think it would be much better if we had a barbecue at the end.//<portrait=happy>Corn, some fish…maybe watermelon?//Doesn’t it sound good?

Text.SourceString: Have you checked out our cat furniture?//Some of those pieces are comfier than my bed. Go ahead. Go in and try sitting on one!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you checked out our cat furniture?//Some of those pieces are comfier than my bed. Go ahead. Go in and try sitting on one!

Text.SourceString: It’s a nice day out.//<portrait=normal>I’m glad I woke up early today.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a nice day out.//<portrait=normal>I’m glad I woke up early today.

Text.SourceString: I gotta head to the Tavern soon.//A full day today, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: I gotta head to the Tavern soon.//A full day today, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: There are some interesting documents in the mayor’s office.//There are some old pictures of the town too.
Text.LocalizedString: There are some interesting documents in the mayor’s office.//There are some old pictures of the town too.

Text.SourceString: I can’t fault <NpcName>Raj</> for opening a coffee shop here in front of the Tavern.//It’s a great spot.//<portrait=surprised>Great coffee too! Dang!
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t fault <NpcName>Raj</> for opening a coffee shop here in front of the Tavern.//It’s a great spot.//<portrait=surprised>Great coffee too! Dang!

Text.SourceString: We don’t sell coconuts.//If you’re looking to buy some, the Beach Shack might have them.//<portrait=happy>We have green tea. What do you say?
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t sell coconuts.//If you’re looking to buy some, the Beach Shack might have them.//<portrait=happy>We have green tea. What do you say?

Text.SourceString: Business has been pretty good lately.//I think the live music really helps.
Text.LocalizedString: Business has been pretty good lately.//I think the live music really helps.

Text.SourceString: The week of New Year’s reminds me of my childhood.//We used to visit Mom’s side of the family, celebrating the traditional way, you know. Wearing red, feasts every day!
Text.LocalizedString: The week of New Year’s reminds me of my childhood.//We used to visit Mom’s side of the family, celebrating the traditional way, you know. Wearing red, feasts every day!

Text.SourceString: Mom isn’t too strict about following tradition.//My grandma would have us in red for the whole week.//<portrait=happy>I love Ama. She’s a character.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom isn’t too strict about following tradition.//My grandma would have us in red for the whole week.//<portrait=happy>I love Ama. She’s a character.

Text.SourceString: She’d be proud that I’m wearing this red shirt.//Good fortune all the way!
Text.LocalizedString: She’d be proud that I’m wearing this red shirt.//Good fortune all the way!

Text.SourceString: It’s been a good year.//<portrait=happy>Mom’s pretty much healthy. Wife and cats happy.//<portrait=surprised>Tried a few new recipes. <Italic>Failed</> a few recipes.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s been a good year.//<portrait=happy>Mom’s pretty much healthy. Wife and cats happy.//<portrait=surprised>Tried a few new recipes. <Italic>Failed</> a few recipes.

Text.SourceString: I keep a second pair of boots in <NpcName>Noah’s</> room.//In case I get soaked walking to work in the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep a second pair of boots in <NpcName>Noah’s</> room.//In case I get soaked walking to work in the snow.

Text.SourceString: So many birds out lately.//Do you think it’s the warm weather? Can’t be.//<portrait=concerned>Well, what else could it be, though?
Text.LocalizedString: So many birds out lately.//Do you think it’s the warm weather? Can’t be.//<portrait=concerned>Well, what else could it be, though?

Text.SourceString: We spent a fortune getting a portrait of <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> painted. And not by just any painter.//<portrait=annoyed>It was a famous pet portraitist. I couldn’t really make out the painting, but… I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: We spent quite a fortune getting a portrait of <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> painted. And not by just any painter.//<portrait=annoyed>It was a famous pet portraitist. I couldn’t really make out the painting, but… I don’t know.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Erika</> and I don’t want kids.//<portrait=happy>We’ve got our cats.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Erika</> and I don’t want kids.//<portrait=happy>We’ve got our cats.

Text.SourceString: Mom wasn’t having it at first, but she came around.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom wasn’t having it at first, but she came around.

Text.SourceString: You should check out the Tavern on the weekend.//<portrait=happy>So, so lively!
